  A type <fr:tex>X</fr:tex> is called <fr:strong>finite</fr:strong> if there exists a natural number
  <fr:tex>n</fr:tex> and a surjective function <fr:tex
display="block">e :  \mathsf {Fin}( n )   \twoheadrightarrow  X.</fr:tex> Such a
  surjective map is called a <fr:em>listing</fr:em> of <fr:tex>X</fr:tex>.
